  "grammarPoint": {
    "title": "No \"to be\" in the present, and \"I want\" = хочу",
    "explanation": "Russian drops **am / is / are** in the present. *Я студент* literally means \"I student\" = I am a student. Just put the words together.\n\n**\"I want\" = хочу**, followed by a noun in the object (accusative) form, or by an infinitive verb.",
    "examples": [
      { "ru": "Я студент.", "en": "I am a student.", "note": "No word for 'am'." },
      { "ru": "Хочу воду.", "en": "I want water.", "note": "воду = object form of вода." },
      { "ru": "Хочу говорить по-русски.", "en": "I want to speak Russian.", "note": "хочу + infinitive." },
      { "ru": "Меня зовут Габриэль.", "en": "My name is Gabriel.", "note": "Idiom: literally 'me they call'." }
    ]
  },

